== About RiseUp Summit == '''RiseUp Summit''' is an annual entrepreneurship and innovation event that takes place in Downtown [[Cairo]], Egypt.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://egyptianstreets.com/2016/11/26/cairo-to-attract-5000-investors-and-entrepreneurs-in-riseup-summit-next-month/|title=Cairo to Attract 5,000 Investors and Entrepreneurs in RiseUp Summit Next Month|date=November 26, 2016|website=[[Egyptian Streets]]|accessdate=February 8, 2017|ref={{sfnref | Egyptian Streets | 2016}}}}</ref> It has been described as "one of the largest gatherings of entrepreneurs in the region". It started in 2013 to bring the MENA region's entrepreneurship ecosystem together.<ref name="Economist 2017">{{cite web|url=https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21714335-arab-entrepreneurs-could-help-many-regions-problems-too-many|title=Startups in the Arab world|date=January 14, 2017|website=[[The Economist]]|accessdate=February 8, 2017}}</ref> The summit is a three-day, entrepreneurship [[marathon]]. The first RiseUp Summit occurred in 2013 and is now in its fifth year.<ref name="Economist 2017" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2016/12/10/riseup-summit-2016-kicks-off-friday/|title=RiseUp Summit 2016 kicks off on Friday|last=El-Din|first=Mohamed Alaa|date=December 10, 2016|website=[[Daily News Egypt]]|accessdate=February 8, 2017}}</ref>
== About RiseUp == {{Orphan|date=February 2017}} RiseUp is a platform that connects startups to the most relevant resources, worldwide.
== Participants == RiseUp participants include some of the world's leading companies, investors, speakers and support organizations.<ref>{{cite web | last=Farid | first=Doaa | title=RiseUp Summit concludes, entrepreneurs receive exposure | website=Daily News Egypt | date=December 13, 2015 | url=http://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2015/12/13/riseup-summit-concludes-entrepreneurs-receive-exposure/ | accessdate=February 8, 2017}}</ref> Previous participating firms include [[Uber (company)|UBER]], [[IBM]], [[Facebook]], The World Bank and Pepsi. Speakers have included [[Dave McClure]] from [[500 Startups|500Startups]], Mike Butcher from [[TechCrunch|Tech Crunch]], Jared Friedman from [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]] and H.E [[List of diplomats of the United Kingdom to Egypt|John Casson]].
== Awards == In 2017, RiseUp was awarded "Ecosystem Player of the Year" given to an organization with the biggest and broadest impact in the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) by [[TechWadi]].
